                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14568541" author="irashid" created="Tue, 2 Jun 2015 05:19:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=joshrosen&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;joshrosen&quot;&gt;joshrosen&lt;/a&gt; and I discussed this a bit, I&apos;m uploading a doc with a discussion of some alternatives.  I am working on exploring the options a little, but would appreciate any feedback on the various options.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14568552" author="irashid" created="Tue, 2 Jun 2015 05:27:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a subset of the issues originally reported in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-7308&quot; title=&quot;Should there be multiple concurrent attempts for one stage?&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-7308&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-7308&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, to have an issue with a smaller scope, but hopefully still large enough to consider the design.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-7829&quot; title=&quot;SortShuffleWriter writes inconsistent data &amp;amp; index files on stage retry&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-7829&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-7829&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is the &quot;ad-hoc&quot; proposal of the fix for this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14573272" author="apachespark" created="Thu, 4 Jun 2015 18:02:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;squito&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/6648&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/6648&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14703567" author="rxin" created="Wed, 19 Aug 2015 18:56:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have retargeted this and downgraded it from Blocker to Critical since it&apos;s been there for a while and not a regression.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14965832" author="rxin" created="Tue, 20 Oct 2015 21:43:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;d be really good to fix this in 1.6, and maybe even backport it to older branches.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=irashid&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;irashid&quot;&gt;irashid&lt;/a&gt; Would you have time to give &quot;Executors Commit ShuffleMapOutput: First Attempt Wins&quot; in your design proposal a try? It seems like a much smaller fix needed, and the chance of that fix having problems is pretty low (despite you think it is &quot;optimistic&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
